UI DESIGN PHILOSOPHY — strictly enforce this
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
The Trendlo store uses a bold dark-first design with orange accents.
Think: Nothing Phone website, Vercel homepage, Supreme store — dark, minimal, 
one powerful accent color, generous white space, clean typography.

Rules for every UI component:
- Header and footer: always dark (#0F0F0F background, white text)
- Hero sections: dark background, orange CTA buttons
- Product pages: light background (#F8F7F4) for readability
- Cart drawer: dark (#1A1A1A background)
- Admin dashboard: light background for data readability
- All primary CTA buttons: #FF6B35 background, white text, slight scale on hover
- All secondary buttons: transparent bg, #FF6B35 border and text
- Hover effects: subtle opacity or scale — no color changes on hover
- Border radius: 8px for buttons and inputs, 12px for cards, 0px for full-width sections
- Font: Inter — weights 400, 500, 600 only. Never 700 or 800.
- Spacing: generous. More padding than you think is needed.
- No gradients except one allowed: linear from #FF6B35 to #FF8C5A on hero CTA button only
- No box shadows on cards — use borders instead
- Images: always show on clean white/light surface so product stands out
- Animations: subtle only. Scale 1.02 on card hover. No bouncing or flashy effects.
- Mobile: every touch target minimum 44px height

TECH STACK — never deviate from this
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Framework   : Next.js 16.1.6 with App Router and TypeScript strict mode
React       : React 19.2
Styling     : Tailwind CSS v4 + shadcn/ui components
